(Getting Started with Docker) Tj

/F2 13 Tf
50 730 Td
(What is Docker?) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
50 710 Td
(Docker is a platform for developing, shipping, and running applications) Tj
50 696 Td
(inside lightweight containers. Containers package your application and its) Tj
50 682 Td
(dependencies together, ensuring it runs the same everywhere.) Tj
50 660 Td
(Unlike virtual machines, containers share the host OS kernel and start in) Tj
50 646 Td
(milliseconds. A typical Node.js app container is 100-200 MB vs a VM at 2+ GB.) Tj
/F2 13 Tf
50 622 Td
(Installing Docker) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
50 602 Td
(On macOS, download Docker Desktop from docker.com/products/docker-desktop.) Tj
50 588 Td
(Install the .dmg and follow the setup wizard. Docker Desktop includes the) Tj
50 574 Td
(Docker Engine, Docker CLI, and Docker Compose.) Tj
50 552 Td
(Verify installation:) Tj
50 538 Td
(docker --version) Tj
50 524 Td
(docker compose version) Tj
50 502 Td
(On Ubuntu Linux:) Tj
50 488 Td
(curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com | sh) Tj
50 474 Td
(sudo usermod -aG docker $USER) Tj
50 460 Td
(newgrp docker) Tj
/F2 13 Tf
50 436 Td
(Core Concepts) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
50 416 Td
(IMAGE: A read-only template used to create containers. Think of it as a) Tj
50 402 Td
(class in object-oriented programming. Images are built from a Dockerfile.) Tj
50 380 Td
(CONTAINER: A running instance of an image. Like an object instantiated) Tj
50 366 Td
(from a class. Containers are isolated but share the host kernel.) Tj
50 344 Td
(DOCKERFILE: A text file with instructions to build an image. Each) Tj
50 330 Td
(instruction adds a layer. Layers are cached, making rebuilds fast.) Tj
50 308 Td
(REGISTRY: A storage and distribution system for images. Docker Hub is the) Tj
50 294 Td
(default public registry. You can run private registries too.) Tj
50 272 Td
(VOLUME: Persistent storage that lives outside the container filesystem.) Tj
50 258 Td
(Data in volumes survives container restarts and deletions.) Tj
50 236 Td
(NETWORK: Containers on the same Docker network can communicate by name.) Tj
50 222 Td
(Docker creates a default bridge network automatically.) Tj
/F2 13 Tf
50 198 Td
(Essential Commands) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
50 178 Td
(Build an image from a Dockerfile in the current directory:) Tj
50 164 Td
(docker build -t myapp:latest .) Tj
50 142 Td
(Run a container from an image:) Tj
50 128 Td
(docker run -d -p 3000:3000 --name myapp myapp:latest) Tj
50 106 Td
(List running containers:) Tj
50 92 Td
(docker ps) Tj
50 70 Td
(Stop and remove a container:) Tj
50 60 Td
(docker logs -f myapp) Tj
50 60 Td
(docker exec -it myapp sh) Tj
50 60 Td
(docker pull postgres:16) Tj
50 60 Td
(docker images) Tj
50 60 Td
(docker image prune -a) Tj
